    "The submandibular lymph nodes on the right are palpable, firm, and immobile.The lesion is tender for palpation.",
    "The panoramic radiograph shows a large, irregularly circumscribed, radiolucent lesion in the right mandibular body and ramus.",
    "Radiographically, the lesion has a mixed radiolucent/radiopaque appearance.",
    "year-old woman presented with a three-month history of painless pigmentation of the left upper anterior gingiva.",
    "There was no history of systemic disease or head and neck trauma."
